<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-21T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-21T02:00:00-05:00" n="89" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/926: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-21T15:00:00+08:00">April 21, 1934—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 21—11:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>187. My 184, April 20, noon. British Legation states that British Foreign
                            Office has instructed it that it is unwilling to retreat from position
                            previously taken which was reported in my 122, March 15, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>